revision.text:
'''Deviation analysis''' may mean;

* in statistics; measurement of the [[absolute difference]] between any one number in a set and the mean of the set.
* in social psychology; monitoring of the behavior of people or objects within systems to measure compliance with expected or desired [[Norm (sociology)|norms]] in order to trigger alerts, identity users or spot anomalies.

